Body Satisfaction at age 14 R markdown

Scoring of the ALSPAC Body Satisfaction Scale at age 14 This scale was developed by ect [include reference] It has been used in ALSPAC in the following studies [include list of studies/refs] An 11 item scale where one item differs between the sexes, two items grade overall body satisfaction (list) while the other nine refer to specific body parts (list). Graded on a 5 point likert scale from Extremely Satisfied (1) to Extremely Dissastisfied (5) Body dissatisfaction was determined with the mean score of all items using one different item in boys vs.girls, with higher scores indicating higher body dissatisfaction.

First we Load the Raw Data

library(haven)
ALSPAC_Raw <- read_sav("ALSPAC.Raw.sav")
View(ALSPAC_Raw)

and then we load the scoresheet

library (readxl)
body_sat_score <- read_excel("scoresheets/body_dissastisfaction_scoresheet_ALSPAC.xlsx") 
View(body_sat_score)

Now we Load in the scorekeeper package and run the scorekeep function


library(scorekeeper)
scored_body_sat <- scorekeep(body_dissat, body_sat_score)
View(scored_body_sat[[5]])

now we will save this into the body satisfaction cleaned data

body_dissatisfaction <- scored_body_sat[[5]]
resave(body_dissatisfaction, file = 'ALSPAC_Cleaned.RData')
scored_body_sat

We now have 15 variables the original raw variables, ID, participant sex, and the means of participant responses. because boys and girls recieved one different item on the scale we expect each participant to be missing one value.
